.TH "ROMAN NUMERAL" 3 "@RELEASE_MONTH@" "@PACKAGE_TARNAME@ @PACKAGE_VERSION@"
.SH NAME
roman \- Roman numeral conversion routines
.SH LIBRARY
Roman Numeral Conversions (libroman, -lroman)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <roman.h>
.sp
.BI "const char * long2roman( unsigned " number ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B long2roman()
function converts
.I number
from an
.I unsigned int
to a 
.I char
pointer that points to memory containing the Roman numeral representation of
the value.
.PP
Subsequent calls to
.B long2roman()
will overwrite previous values.
.SH RETURN VALUES
If successful, 
.B long2roman
returns a pointer to a string containing the Roman numeral equivalent. If there
is an error, it will return a
.B NULL
pointer and sets
.I errno
to indicate the error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B EDOM
.I number
is too large to be represented using this method.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR roman (1),
.BR roman2long (3)
.BR roman_ctime (3)
.SH REPORTING BUGS
Report bugs to <@PACKAGE_BUGREPORT@>.
.\" end of man page
